cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY. 

The paper presents a machine learning framework for multi-agent systems to learn both the optimal policy for maximizing the rewards and the encoding of the high dimensional visual observation. This involves using reinforcement learning and encoding techniques for visual observations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with multi-agent robotic systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper involves using communication between agents, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The encoding of visual observations could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves using reinforcement learning to solve a problem, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
